    • Method Detail

      • testHashCode

        public void testHashCode()
        Test the hashing for a vertex.

        Makes sure that two vertices with identical coordinates have the same hashcode but that two vertices with different coordinates have different hashcodes.

      • testVertex

        public void testVertex()
        Test the default constructor for a vertex.

        Makes sure that the constructed vertex is not null and has the expected x=0 and y=0 as coordinates.

      • testVertexIntInt

        public void testVertexIntInt()
        Test the custom constructor for a vertex.

        Makes sure that the constructed vertex is not null and has the provided x and y as coordinates.

      • testToString

        public void testToString()
        Test the conversion to string method.

        Makes sure that the returned string is neither null nor empty.

      • testEqualsObject

        public void testEqualsObject()
        Test the equality comparison method.

        Makes sure that the comparison returns true when two different vertices with the same coordinates are compared to each other and returns false if they have different coordinates.

        Tests that the result is the same if A is compared to B and if B is compared to A.

        Tests that a vertex comparing to itself always return true. Tests that a comparison to null always returns false.

      • testCompareTo

        public void testCompareTo()
        Test the distance-based comparison method.

        Makes sure that the method always returns the grid based distance between any two vertices in any order.

        Tests that the distance between a vertex and itself is 0. Comparisons to null are not handled.
